==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''cornū cōpiae'', horn of plenty.

===Pronunciation===
*(US)
**{{IPA|/ˌkɔrn(j)əˈkoʊpiə/}}
**{{SAMPA|/%kOrn(j)@"koUpi@/}}

===Noun===
'''cornucopia'''
#(''Greek mythology'') a [[goat]]'s [[horn]] [[endlessly]] [[overflowing]] with [[fruit]], [[flower]]s and [[grain]]; or full of whatever its owner wanted
# A hollow horn- or [[cone]]-shaped object, filled with edible or useful things
# An [[abundance]] or plentiful supply.

